\fI?GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_RECTANGLE\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a single value, the name of the texture currently bound to the target \fI?GL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE\fR\&\&. The initial value is 0\&. See \fBgl:bindTexture/2\fR\& \&.
