.RS
.LP
Create or replace a display list
.LP
Display lists are groups of GL commands that have been stored for subsequent execution\&. Display lists are created with \fIgl:newList\fR\&\&. All subsequent commands are placed in the display list, in the order issued, until \fBgl:endList/0\fR\& is called\&.
.LP
\fIgl:newList\fR\& has two arguments\&. The first argument, \fIList\fR\& , is a positive integer that becomes the unique name for the display list\&. Names can be created and reserved with \fBgl:genLists/1\fR\& and tested for uniqueness with \fBgl:isList/1\fR\& \&. The second argument, \fIMode\fR\& , is a symbolic constant that can assume one of two values:
.LP
\fI?GL_COMPILE\fR\&: Commands are merely compiled\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_COMPILE_AND_EXECUTE\fR\&: Commands are executed as they are compiled into the display list\&.
.LP
Certain commands are not compiled into the display list but are executed immediately, regardless of the display-list mode\&. These commands are \fBgl:areTexturesResident/1\fR\& , \fBgl:colorPointer/4\fR\& , \fBgl:deleteLists/2\fR\& , \fBgl:deleteTextures/1\fR\& , \fBgl:enableClientState/1\fR\& , \fBgl:edgeFlagPointer/2\fR\& , \fBgl:enableClientState/1\fR\& , \fBgl:feedbackBuffer/3\fR\& , \fBgl:finish/0\fR\& , \fBgl:flush/0\fR\& , \fBgl:genLists/1\fR\& , \fBgl:genTextures/1\fR\& , \fBgl:indexPointer/3\fR\& , \fBgl:interleavedArrays/3\fR\& , \fBgl:isEnabled/1\fR\& , \fBgl:isList/1\fR\& , \fBgl:isTexture/1\fR\& , \fBgl:normalPointer/3\fR\& , \fBgl:pushClientAttrib/1\fR\& , \fBgl:pixelStoref/2\fR\& , \fBgl:pushClientAttrib/1\fR\& , \fBgl:readPixels/7\fR\& , \fBgl:renderMode/1\fR\& , \fBgl:selectBuffer/2\fR\& , \fBgl:texCoordPointer/4\fR\& , \fBgl:vertexPointer/4\fR\& , and all of the \fBgl:getBooleanv/1\fR\& commands\&.
.LP
Similarly, \fBgl:texImage1D/8\fR\& , \fBgl:texImage2D/9\fR\& , and \fBgl:texImage3D/10\fR\& are executed immediately and not compiled into the display list when their first argument is \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_1D\fR\&, \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_1D\fR\&, or \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_3D\fR\& , respectively\&.
.LP
When the ARB_imaging extension is supported, \fBgl:histogram/4\fR\& executes immediately when its argument is \fI?GL_PROXY_HISTOGRAM\fR\&\&. Similarly, \fBgl:colorTable/6\fR\& executes immediately when its first argument is \fI?GL_PROXY_COLOR_TABLE\fR\&, \fI?GL_PROXY_POST_CONVOLUTION_COLOR_TABLE\fR\& , or \fI?GL_PROXY_POST_COLOR_MATRIX_COLOR_TABLE\fR\&\&.
.LP
For OpenGL versions 1\&.3 and greater, or when the ARB_multitexture extension is supported, \fBgl:clientActiveTexture/1\fR\& is not compiled into display lists, but executed immediately\&.
.LP
When \fBgl:endList/0\fR\& is encountered, the display-list definition is completed by associating the list with the unique name \fIList\fR\& (specified in the \fIgl:newList\fR\& command)\&. If a display list with name \fIList\fR\& already exists, it is replaced only when \fBgl:endList/0\fR\& is called\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
