.RS 3
X = float()
.br
Y = float()
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Specify the raster position for pixel operations
.LP
The GL maintains a 3D position in window coordinates\&. This position, called the raster position, is used to position pixel and bitmap write operations\&. It is maintained with subpixel accuracy\&. See \fBgl:bitmap/7\fR\& , \fBgl:drawPixels/5\fR\& , and \fBgl:copyPixels/5\fR\& \&.
.LP
The current raster position consists of three window coordinates ( x, y, z), a clip coordinate value ( w), an eye coordinate distance, a valid bit, and associated color data and texture coordinates\&. The w coordinate is a clip coordinate, because w is not projected to window coordinates\&. \fIgl:rasterPos4\fR\& specifies object coordinates x, y, z, and w explicitly\&. \fIgl:rasterPos3\fR\& specifies object coordinate x, y, and z explicitly, while w is implicitly set to 1\&. \fIgl:rasterPos2\fR\& uses the argument values for x and y while implicitly setting z and w to 0 and 1\&.
.LP
The object coordinates presented by \fIgl:rasterPos\fR\& are treated just like those of a \fBgl:vertex2d/2\fR\& command: They are transformed by the current modelview and projection matrices and passed to the clipping stage\&. If the vertex is not culled, then it is projected and scaled to window coordinates, which become the new current raster position, and the \fI?GL_CURRENT_RASTER_POSITION_VALID\fR\& flag is set\&. If the vertex \fIis\fR\& culled, then the valid bit is cleared and the current raster position and associated color and texture coordinates are undefined\&.
.LP
The current raster position also includes some associated color data and texture coordinates\&. If lighting is enabled, then \fI?GL_CURRENT_RASTER_COLOR\fR\& (in RGBA mode) or \fI?GL_CURRENT_RASTER_INDEX\fR\& (in color index mode) is set to the color produced by the lighting calculation (see \fBgl:lightf/3\fR\& , \fBgl:lightModelf/2\fR\& , and \fBgl:shadeModel/1\fR\& )\&. If lighting is disabled, current color (in RGBA mode, state variable \fI?GL_CURRENT_COLOR\fR\&) or color index (in color index mode, state variable \fI?GL_CURRENT_INDEX\fR\&) is used to update the current raster color\&. \fI?GL_CURRENT_RASTER_SECONDARY_COLOR\fR\& (in RGBA mode) is likewise updated\&.
.LP
Likewise, \fI?GL_CURRENT_RASTER_TEXTURE_COORDS\fR\& is updated as a function of \fI?GL_CURRENT_TEXTURE_COORDS\fR\& , based on the texture matrix and the texture generation functions (see \fBgl:texGend/3\fR\& )\&. Finally, the distance from the origin of the eye coordinate system to the vertex as transformed by only the modelview matrix replaces \fI?GL_CURRENT_RASTER_DISTANCE\fR\&\&.
.LP
Initially, the current raster position is (0, 0, 0, 1), the current raster distance is 0, the valid bit is set, the associated RGBA color is (1, 1, 1, 1), the associated color index is 1, and the associated texture coordinates are (0, 0, 0, 1)\&. In RGBA mode, \fI?GL_CURRENT_RASTER_INDEX\fR\& is always 1; in color index mode, the current raster RGBA color always maintains its initial value\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
