.LP
Specify the pixel zoom factors
.LP
\fIgl:pixelZoom\fR\& specifies values for the x and y zoom factors\&. During the execution of \fBgl:drawPixels/5\fR\& or \fBgl:copyPixels/5\fR\& , if ( xr, yr) is the current raster position, and a given element is in the mth row and nth column of the pixel rectangle, then pixels whose centers are in the rectangle with corners at
.LP
( xr+n\&. xfactor, yr+m\&. yfactor)
.LP
( xr+(n+1)\&. xfactor, yr+(m+1)\&. yfactor)
.LP
are candidates for replacement\&. Any pixel whose center lies on the bottom or left edge of this rectangular region is also modified\&.
.LP
Pixel zoom factors are not limited to positive values\&. Negative zoom factors reflect the resulting image about the current raster position\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
