.LP
Set up pixel transfer maps
.LP
\fIgl:pixelMap\fR\& sets up translation tables, or \fImaps\fR\&, used by \fBgl:copyPixels/5\fR\& , \fBgl:copyTexImage1D/7\fR\& , \fBgl:copyTexImage2D/8\fR\& , \fBgl:copyTexSubImage1D/6\fR\& , \fBgl:copyTexSubImage2D/8\fR\& , \fBgl:copyTexSubImage3D/9\fR\& , \fBgl:drawPixels/5\fR\& , \fBgl:readPixels/7\fR\& , \fBgl:texImage1D/8\fR\& , \fBgl:texImage2D/9\fR\& , \fBgl:texImage3D/10\fR\& , \fBgl:texSubImage1D/7\fR\& , \fBgl:texSubImage1D/7\fR\& , and \fBgl:texSubImage1D/7\fR\& \&. Additionally, if the ARB_imaging subset is supported, the routines \fBgl:colorTable/6\fR\& , \fBgl:colorSubTable/6\fR\& , \fBgl:convolutionFilter1D/6\fR\& , \fBgl:convolutionFilter2D/7\fR\& , \fBgl:histogram/4\fR\& , \fBgl:minmax/3\fR\& , and \fBgl:separableFilter2D/8\fR\& \&. Use of these maps is described completely in the \fBgl:pixelTransferf/2\fR\& reference page, and partly in the reference pages for the pixel and texture image commands\&. Only the specification of the maps is described in this reference page\&.
.LP
\fIMap\fR\& is a symbolic map name, indicating one of ten maps to set\&. \fIMapsize\fR\& specifies the number of entries in the map, and \fIValues\fR\& is a pointer to an array of \fIMapsize\fR\& map values\&.
.LP
If a non-zero named buffer object is bound to the \fI?GL_PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER\fR\& target (see \fBgl:bindBuffer/2\fR\& ) while a pixel transfer map is specified, \fIValues\fR\& is treated as a byte offset into the buffer object\&'s data store\&.
.LP
The ten maps are as follows:
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_I_TO_I\fR\&: Maps color indices to color indices\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_S_TO_S\fR\&: Maps stencil indices to stencil indices\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_I_TO_R\fR\&: Maps color indices to red components\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_I_TO_G\fR\&: Maps color indices to green components\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_I_TO_B\fR\&: Maps color indices to blue components\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_I_TO_A\fR\&: Maps color indices to alpha components\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_R_TO_R\fR\&: Maps red components to red components\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_G_TO_G\fR\&: Maps green components to green components\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_B_TO_B\fR\&: Maps blue components to blue components\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_A_TO_A\fR\&: Maps alpha components to alpha components\&.
.LP
