.LP
Maps that store indices, \fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_I_TO_I\fR\& and \fI?GL_PIXEL_MAP_S_TO_S\fR\&, retain their values in fixed-point format, with an unspecified number of bits to the right of the binary point\&. Floating-point values specified by \fIgl:pixelMapfv\fR\& are converted directly to the internal fixed-point format of these maps\&. Unsigned integer values specified by \fIgl:pixelMapusv\fR\& and \fIgl:pixelMapuiv\fR\& specify integer values, with all 0\&'s to the right of the binary point\&.
