.LP
The rasterization described so far assumes pixel zoom factors of 1\&. If \fBgl:pixelZoom/2\fR\& is used to change the x and y pixel zoom factors, pixels are converted to fragments as follows\&. If (x r y r) is the current raster position, and a given pixel is in the nth column and mth row of the pixel rectangle, then fragments are generated for pixels whose centers are in the rectangle with corners at
.LP
(x r+(zoom x) n y r+(zoom y) m)
