.LP
Return texture environment parameters
.LP
\fIgl:getTexEnv\fR\& returns in \fIParams\fR\& selected values of a texture environment that was specified with \fBgl:texEnvfv/3\fR\& \&. \fITarget\fR\& specifies a texture environment\&.
.LP
When \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TEXTURE_FILTER_CONTROL\fR\&, \fIPname\fR\& must be \fI?GL_TEXTURE_LOD_BIAS\fR\& \&. When \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_POINT_SPRITE\fR\&, \fIPname\fR\& must be \fI?GL_COORD_REPLACE\fR\& \&. When \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TEXTURE_ENV\fR\&, \fIPname\fR\& can be \fI?GL_TEXTURE_ENV_MODE\fR\& , \fI?GL_TEXTURE_ENV_COLOR\fR\&, \fI?GL_COMBINE_RGB\fR\&, \fI?GL_COMBINE_ALPHA\fR\&, \fI?GL_RGB_SCALE\fR\& , \fI?GL_ALPHA_SCALE\fR\&, \fI?GL_SRC0_RGB\fR\&, \fI?GL_SRC1_RGB\fR\&, \fI?GL_SRC2_RGB\fR\&, \fI?GL_SRC0_ALPHA\fR\&, \fI?GL_SRC1_ALPHA\fR\&, or \fI?GL_SRC2_ALPHA\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fIPname\fR\& names a specific texture environment parameter, as follows:
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_ENV_MODE\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the single-valued texture environment mode, a symbolic constant\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_MODULATE\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_ENV_COLOR\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns four integer or floating-point values that are the texture environment color\&. Integer values, when requested, are linearly mapped from the internal floating-point representation such that 1\&.0 maps to the most positive representable integer, and -1\&.0 maps to the most negative representable integer\&. The initial value is (0, 0, 0, 0)\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_LOD_BIAS\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a single floating-point value that is the texture level-of-detail bias\&. The initial value is 0\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_COMBINE_RGB\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a single symbolic constant value representing the current RGB combine mode\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_MODULATE\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_COMBINE_ALPHA\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a single symbolic constant value representing the current alpha combine mode\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_MODULATE\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_SRC0_RGB\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a single symbolic constant value representing the texture combiner zero\&'s RGB source\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_TEXTURE\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_SRC1_RGB\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a single symbolic constant value representing the texture combiner one\&'s RGB source\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_PREVIOUS\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_SRC2_RGB\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a single symbolic constant value representing the texture combiner two\&'s RGB source\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_CONSTANT\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_SRC0_ALPHA\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a single symbolic constant value representing the texture combiner zero\&'s alpha source\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_TEXTURE\fR\&\&.
.LP
