.LP
Assume c s is the sRGB component in the range [0,1]\&.
.LP
Use the \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_2D\fR\&, \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_1D_ARRAY\fR\&, \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE\fR\& , or \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP\fR\& target to try out a resolution and format\&. The implementation will update and recompute its best match for the requested storage resolution and format\&. To then query this state, call \fBgl:getTexLevelParameterfv/3\fR\& \&. If the texture cannot be accommodated, texture state is set to 0\&.
.LP
A one-component texture image uses only the red component of the RGBA color extracted from \fIData\fR\& \&. A two-component image uses the R and G values\&. A three-component image uses the R, G, and B values\&. A four-component image uses all of the RGBA components\&.
