.LP
Delete named textures
.LP
\fIgl:deleteTextures\fR\& deletes \fIN\fR\& textures named by the elements of the array \fITextures\fR\& \&. After a texture is deleted, it has no contents or dimensionality, and its name is free for reuse (for example by \fBgl:genTextures/1\fR\& )\&. If a texture that is currently bound is deleted, the binding reverts to 0 (the default texture)\&.
.LP
\fIgl:deleteTextures\fR\& silently ignores 0\&'s and names that do not correspond to existing textures\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
