.LP
GL establishes a \fIworking set\fR\& of textures that are resident in texture memory\&. These textures can be bound to a texture target much more efficiently than textures that are not resident\&.
.LP
\fIgl:areTexturesResident\fR\& queries the texture residence status of the \fIN\fR\& textures named by the elements of \fITextures\fR\& \&. If all the named textures are resident, \fIgl:areTexturesResident\fR\& returns \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\&, and the contents of \fIResidences\fR\& are undisturbed\&. If not all the named textures are resident, \fIgl:areTexturesResident\fR\& returns \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\&, and detailed status is returned in the \fIN\fR\& elements of \fIResidences\fR\& \&. If an element of \fIResidences\fR\& is \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\&, then the texture named by the corresponding element of \fITextures\fR\& is resident\&.
