The \fI?GL_BLEND_COLOR\fR\& may be used to calculate the source and destination blending factors\&. The color components are clamped to the range [0 1] before being stored\&. See \fBgl:blendFunc/2\fR\& for a complete description of the blending operations\&. Initially the \fI?GL_BLEND_COLOR\fR\& is set to (0, 0, 0, 0)\&.
