The pixels in the rectangle are processed exactly as if \fBgl:readPixels/7\fR\& had been called with \fIformat\fR\& set to RGBA, but the process stops just before final conversion\&. The R, G, B, and A components of each pixel are next scaled by the four 2D \fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_FILTER_SCALE\fR\& parameters and biased by the four 2D \fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_FILTER_BIAS\fR\& parameters\&. (The scale and bias parameters are set by \fBgl:convolutionParameterf/3\fR\& using the \fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_2D\fR\& target and the names \fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_FILTER_SCALE\fR\& and \fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_FILTER_BIAS\fR\& \&. The parameters themselves are vectors of four values that are applied to red, green, blue, and alpha, in that order\&.) The R, G, B, and A values are not clamped to [0,1] at any time during this process\&.
.LP
Each pixel is then converted to the internal format specified by \fIInternalformat\fR\& \&. This conversion simply maps the component values of the pixel (R, G, B, and A) to the values included in the internal format (red, green, blue, alpha, luminance, and intensity)\&. The mapping is as follows:\fIInternal Format\fR\&\fIRed\fR\&\fIGreen\fR\&\fIBlue\fR\&\fIAlpha\fR\&\fILuminance\fR\&\fIIntensity\fR\&
.br
\fI?GL_ALPHA\fR\& A 
.br
\fI?GL_LUMINANCE\fR\& R 
.br
\fI?GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA\fR\& A R 
.br
\fI?GL_INTENSITY\fR\& R 
.br
\fI?GL_RGB\fR\& R G B 
.br
\fI?GL_RGBA\fR\& R G B A 
.br

.LP
The red, green, blue, alpha, luminance, and/or intensity components of the resulting pixels are stored in floating-point rather than integer format\&.
.LP
Pixel ordering is such that lower x screen coordinates correspond to lower \fIi\fR\& filter image coordinates, and lower y screen coordinates correspond to lower \fIj\fR\& filter image coordinates\&.
.LP
Note that after a convolution is performed, the resulting color components are also scaled by their corresponding \fI?GL_POST_CONVOLUTION_c_SCALE\fR\& parameters and biased by their corresponding \fI?GL_POST_CONVOLUTION_c_BIAS\fR\& parameters (where \fIc\fR\& takes on the values \fIRED\fR\&, \fIGREEN\fR\&, \fIBLUE\fR\&, and \fIALPHA\fR\&)\&. These parameters are set by \fBgl:pixelTransferf/2\fR\& \&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
.B
