.LP
\fIgl:getConvolutionParameter\fR\& retrieves convolution parameters\&. \fITarget\fR\& determines which convolution filter is queried\&. \fIPname\fR\& determines which parameter is returned:
.LP
\fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_BORDER_MODE\fR\&: The convolution border mode\&. See \fBgl:convolutionParameterf/3\fR\& for a list of border modes\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_BORDER_COLOR\fR\&: The current convolution border color\&. \fIParams\fR\& must be a pointer to an array of four elements, which will receive the red, green, blue, and alpha border colors\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_FILTER_SCALE\fR\&: The current filter scale factors\&. \fIParams\fR\& must be a pointer to an array of four elements, which will receive the red, green, blue, and alpha filter scale factors in that order\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_FILTER_BIAS\fR\&: The current filter bias factors\&. \fIParams\fR\& must be a pointer to an array of four elements, which will receive the red, green, blue, and alpha filter bias terms in that order\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_FORMAT\fR\&: The current internal format\&. See \fBgl:convolutionFilter1D/6\fR\& , \fBgl:convolutionFilter2D/7\fR\& , and \fBgl:separableFilter2D/8\fR\& for lists of allowable formats\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_WIDTH\fR\&: The current filter image width\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_CONVOLUTION_HEIGHT\fR\&: The current filter image height\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_MAX_CONVOLUTION_WIDTH\fR\&: The maximum acceptable filter image width\&.
