.LP
.B
sampleCoverage(Value, Invert) -> ok
.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Value = clamp()
.br
Invert = 0 | 1
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Specify multisample coverage parameters
.LP
Multisampling samples a pixel multiple times at various implementation-dependent subpixel locations to generate antialiasing effects\&. Multisampling transparently antialiases points, lines, polygons, and images if it is enabled\&.
.LP
\fIValue\fR\& is used in constructing a temporary mask used in determining which samples will be used in resolving the final fragment color\&. This mask is bitwise-anded with the coverage mask generated from the multisampling computation\&. If the \fIInvert\fR\& flag is set, the temporary mask is inverted (all bits flipped) and then the bitwise-and is computed\&.
.LP
If an implementation does not have any multisample buffers available, or multisampling is disabled, rasterization occurs with only a single sample computing a pixel\&'s final RGB color\&.
.LP
Provided an implementation supports multisample buffers, and multisampling is enabled, then a pixel\&'s final color is generated by combining several samples per pixel\&. Each sample contains color, depth, and stencil information, allowing those operations to be performed on each sample\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
.B
compressedTexImage3D(Target, Level, Internalformat, Width, Height, Depth, Border, ImageSize, Data) -> ok
.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Target = enum()
.br
Level = integer()
.br
Internalformat = enum()
.br
Width = integer()
.br
Height = integer()
.br
Depth = integer()
.br
Border = integer()
.br
ImageSize = integer()
.br
Data = offset() | mem()
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Specify a three-dimensional texture image in a compressed format
.LP
Texturing allows elements of an image array to be read by shaders\&.
.LP
\fIgl:compressedTexImage3D\fR\& loads a previously defined, and retrieved, compressed three-dimensional texture image if \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TEXTURE_3D\fR\& (see \fBgl:texImage3D/10\fR\& )\&.
.LP
If \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY\fR\&, \fIData\fR\& is treated as an array of compressed 2D textures\&.
.LP
If \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_3D\fR\& or \fI?GL_PROXY_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY\fR\&, no data is read from \fIData\fR\& , but all of the texture image state is recalculated, checked for consistency, and checked against the implementation\&'s capabilities\&. If the implementation cannot handle a texture of the requested texture size, it sets all of the image state to 0, but does not generate an error (see \fBgl:getError/0\fR\& )\&. To query for an entire mipmap array, use an image array level greater than or equal to 1\&.
.LP
\fIInternalformat\fR\& must be a known compressed image format (such as \fI?GL_RGTC\fR\&) or an extension-specified compressed-texture format\&. When a texture is loaded with \fBgl:texImage2D/9\fR\& using a generic compressed texture format (e\&.g\&., \fI?GL_COMPRESSED_RGB\fR\&), the GL selects from one of its extensions supporting compressed textures\&. In order to load the compressed texture image using \fIgl:compressedTexImage3D\fR\&, query the compressed texture image\&'s size and format using \fBgl:getTexLevelParameterfv/3\fR\& \&.
.LP
