.RS
.LP
Detaches a shader object from a program object to which it is attached
.LP
\fIgl:detachShader\fR\& detaches the shader object specified by \fIShader\fR\& from the program object specified by \fIProgram\fR\& \&. This command can be used to undo the effect of the command \fBgl:attachShader/2\fR\& \&.
.LP
If \fIShader\fR\& has already been flagged for deletion by a call to \fBgl:deleteShader/1\fR\& and it is not attached to any other program object, it will be deleted after it has been detached\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
