.LP
Returns a parameter from a program object
.LP
\fIgl:getProgram\fR\& returns in \fIParams\fR\& the value of a parameter for a specific program object\&. The following parameters are defined:
.LP
\fI?GL_DELETE_STATUS\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& if \fIProgram\fR\& is currently flagged for deletion, and \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\& otherwise\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_LINK_STATUS\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& if the last link operation on \fIProgram\fR\& was successful, and \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\& otherwise\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_VALIDATE_STATUS\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& or if the last validation operation on \fIProgram\fR\& was successful, and \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\& otherwise\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_INFO_LOG_LENGTH\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the number of characters in the information log for \fIProgram\fR\& including the null termination character (i\&.e\&., the size of the character buffer required to store the information log)\&. If \fIProgram\fR\& has no information log, a value of 0 is returned\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_ATTACHED_SHADERS\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the number of shader objects attached to \fIProgram\fR\& \&.
.LP
\fI?GL_ACTIVE_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFERS\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the number of active attribute atomic counter buffers used by \fIProgram\fR\& \&.
.LP
\fI?GL_ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTES\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the number of active attribute variables for \fIProgram\fR\& \&.
.LP
\fI?GL_ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTE_MAX_LENGTH\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the length of the longest active attribute name for \fIProgram\fR\& , including the null termination character (i\&.e\&., the size of the character buffer required to store the longest attribute name)\&. If no active attributes exist, 0 is returned\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORMS\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the number of active uniform variables for \fIProgram\fR\& \&.
.LP
\fI?GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_MAX_LENGTH\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the length of the longest active uniform variable name for \fIProgram\fR\& , including the null termination character (i\&.e\&., the size of the character buffer required to store the longest uniform variable name)\&. If no active uniform variables exist, 0 is returned\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_LENGTH\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the length of the program binary, in bytes that will be returned by a call to \fBgl:getProgramBinary/2\fR\& \&. When a progam\&'s \fI?GL_LINK_STATUS\fR\& is \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\&, its program binary length is zero\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER_MODE\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a symbolic constant indicating the buffer mode used when transform feedback is active\&. This may be \fI?GL_SEPARATE_ATTRIBS\fR\& or \fI?GL_INTERLEAVED_ATTRIBS\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYINGS\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the number of varying variables to capture in transform feedback mode for the program\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYING_MAX_LENGTH\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the length of the longest variable name to be used for transform feedback, including the null-terminator\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_GEOMETRY_VERTICES_OUT\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns the maximum number of vertices that the geometry shader in \fIProgram\fR\& will output\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_GEOMETRY_INPUT_TYPE\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a symbolic constant indicating the primitive type accepted as input to the geometry shader contained in \fIProgram\fR\& \&.
.LP
\fI?GL_GEOMETRY_OUTPUT_TYPE\fR\&: \fIParams\fR\& returns a symbolic constant indicating the primitive type that will be output by the geometry shader contained in \fIProgram\fR\& \&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
.B
getProgramInfoLog(Program, BufSize) -> string()
.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Program = integer()
.br
BufSize = integer()
.br
