.LP
Define an array of generic vertex attribute data
.LP
\fIgl:vertexAttribPointer\fR\&, \fIgl:vertexAttribIPointer\fR\& and \fIgl:vertexAttribLPointer\fR\& specify the location and data format of the array of generic vertex attributes at index \fIIndex\fR\& to use when rendering\&. \fISize\fR\& specifies the number of components per attribute and must be 1, 2, 3, 4, or \fI?GL_BGRA\fR\&\&. \fIType\fR\& specifies the data type of each component, and \fIStride\fR\& specifies the byte stride from one attribute to the next, allowing vertices and attributes to be packed into a single array or stored in separate arrays\&.
.LP
For \fIgl:vertexAttribPointer\fR\&, if \fINormalized\fR\& is set to \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\&, it indicates that values stored in an integer format are to be mapped to the range [-1,1] (for signed values) or [0,1] (for unsigned values) when they are accessed and converted to floating point\&. Otherwise, values will be converted to floats directly without normalization\&.
.LP
For \fIgl:vertexAttribIPointer\fR\&, only the integer types \fI?GL_BYTE\fR\&, \fI?GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE\fR\& , \fI?GL_SHORT\fR\&, \fI?GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT\fR\&, \fI?GL_INT\fR\&, \fI?GL_UNSIGNED_INT\fR\& are accepted\&. Values are always left as integer values\&.
.LP
\fIgl:vertexAttribLPointer\fR\& specifies state for a generic vertex attribute array associated with a shader attribute variable declared with 64-bit double precision components\&. \fIType\fR\& must be \fI?GL_DOUBLE\fR\&\&. \fIIndex\fR\& , \fISize\fR\& , and \fIStride\fR\& behave as described for \fIgl:vertexAttribPointer\fR\& and \fIgl:vertexAttribIPointer\fR\&\&.
.LP
If \fIPointer\fR\& is not NULL, a non-zero named buffer object must be bound to the \fI?GL_ARRAY_BUFFER\fR\& target (see \fBgl:bindBuffer/2\fR\& ), otherwise an error is generated\&. \fIPointer\fR\& is treated as a byte offset into the buffer object\&'s data store\&. The buffer object binding (\fI?GL_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING\fR\&) is saved as generic vertex attribute array state (\fI?GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING\fR\& ) for index \fIIndex\fR\& \&.
.LP
When a generic vertex attribute array is specified, \fISize\fR\& , \fIType\fR\& , \fINormalized\fR\& , \fIStride\fR\& , and \fIPointer\fR\& are saved as vertex array state, in addition to the current vertex array buffer object binding\&.
.LP
To enable and disable a generic vertex attribute array, call \fBgl:disableVertexAttribArray/1\fR\& and \fBgl:disableVertexAttribArray/1\fR\& with \fIIndex\fR\& \&. If enabled, the generic vertex attribute array is used when \fBgl:drawArrays/3\fR\& , \fBgl:multiDrawArrays/3\fR\& , \fBgl:drawElements/4\fR\& , see \fIglMultiDrawElements\fR\&, or \fBgl:drawRangeElements/6\fR\& is called\&.
