.LP
\fIgl:bindFragDataLocation\fR\& explicitly specifies the binding of the user-defined varying out variable \fIName\fR\& to fragment shader color number \fIColorNumber\fR\& for program \fIProgram\fR\& \&. If \fIName\fR\& was bound previously, its assigned binding is replaced with \fIColorNumber\fR\& \&. \fIName\fR\& must be a null-terminated string\&. \fIColorNumber\fR\& must be less than \fI?GL_MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS\fR\& \&.
.LP
