.LP
Attach a level of a texture object as a logical buffer to the currently bound framebuffer object
.LP
\fIgl:framebufferTexture\fR\&, \fIgl:framebufferTexture1D\fR\&, \fIgl:framebufferTexture2D\fR\&, and \fIgl:framebufferTexture\fR\& attach a selected mipmap level or image of a texture object as one of the logical buffers of the framebuffer object currently bound to \fITarget\fR\& \&. \fITarget\fR\& must be \fI?GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\&, \fI?GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\&, or \fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\& \&. \fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\& is equivalent to \fI?GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fIAttachment\fR\& specifies the logical attachment of the framebuffer and must be \fI?GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT\fR\& \fIi\fR\&, \fI?GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT\fR\&, \fI?GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT\fR\& or \fI?GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMMENT\fR\& \&. \fIi\fR\& in \fI?GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT\fR\&\fIi\fR\& may range from zero to the value of \fI?GL_MAX_COLOR_ATTACHMENTS\fR\& - 1\&. Attaching a level of a texture to \fI?GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT\fR\& is equivalent to attaching that level to both the \fI?GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT\fR\&\fIand\fR\& the \fI?GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT\fR\& attachment points simultaneously\&.
.LP
\fITextarget\fR\& specifies what type of texture is named by \fITexture\fR\& , and for cube map textures, specifies the face that is to be attached\&. If \fITexture\fR\& is not zero, it must be the name of an existing texture with type \fITextarget\fR\& , unless it is a cube map texture, in which case \fITextarget\fR\& must be \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X\fR\& \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y\fR\& , \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z\fR\&, or \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z\fR\&\&.
.LP
If \fITexture\fR\& is non-zero, the specified \fILevel\fR\& of the texture object named \fITexture\fR\& is attached to the framebfufer attachment point named by \fIAttachment\fR\& \&. For \fIgl:framebufferTexture1D\fR\& , \fIgl:framebufferTexture2D\fR\&, and \fIgl:framebufferTexture3D\fR\&, \fITexture\fR\& must be zero or the name of an existing texture with a target of \fITextarget\fR\& , or \fITexture\fR\& must be the name of an existing cube-map texture and \fITextarget\fR\& must be one of \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X\fR\& , \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X\fR\& , \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y\fR\&, or \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z\fR\&\&.
.LP
If \fITextarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_2D_MULTISAMPLE\fR\&, or \fI?GL_TEXTURE_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY\fR\&, then \fILevel\fR\& must be zero\&. If \fITextarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TEXTURE_3D\fR\&, then level must be greater than or equal to zero and less than or equal to log2 of the value of \fI?GL_MAX_3D_TEXTURE_SIZE\fR\&\&. If \fITextarget\fR\& is one of \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z\fR\& , \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y\fR\&, or \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z\fR\& , then \fILevel\fR\& must be greater than or equal to zero and less than or equal to log2 of the value of \fI?GL_MAX_CUBE_MAP_TEXTURE_SIZE\fR\&\&. For all other values of \fITextarget\fR\& , \fILevel\fR\& must be greater than or equal to zero and no larger than log2 of the value of \fI?GL_MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fILayer\fR\& specifies the layer of a 2-dimensional image within a 3-dimensional texture\&.
.LP
For \fIgl:framebufferTexture1D\fR\&, if \fITexture\fR\& is not zero, then \fITextarget\fR\& must be \fI?GL_TEXTURE_1D\fR\&\&. For \fIgl:framebufferTexture2D\fR\&, if \fITexture\fR\& is not zero, \fITextarget\fR\& must be one of \fI?GL_TEXTURE_2D\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE\fR\& , \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z\fR\& , \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y\fR\&, \fI?GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z\fR\& , or \fI?GL_TEXTURE_2D_MULTISAMPLE\fR\&\&. For \fIgl:framebufferTexture3D\fR\&, if \fITexture\fR\& is not zero, then \fITextarget\fR\& must be \fI?GL_TEXTURE_3D\fR\&\&.
.LP
