.LP
\fIgl:minSampleShading\fR\& specifies the rate at which samples are shaded within a covered pixel\&. Sample-rate shading is enabled by calling \fBgl:enable/1\fR\& with the parameter \fI?GL_SAMPLE_SHADING\fR\& \&. If \fI?GL_MULTISAMPLE\fR\& or \fI?GL_SAMPLE_SHADING\fR\& is disabled, sample shading has no effect\&. Otherwise, an implementation must provide at least as many unique color values for each covered fragment as specified by \fIValue\fR\& times \fISamples\fR\& where \fISamples\fR\& is the value of \fI?GL_SAMPLES\fR\& for the current framebuffer\&. At least 1 sample for each covered fragment is generated\&.
.LP
