\fIgl:checkFramebufferStatus\fR\& queries the completeness status of the framebuffer object currently bound to \fITarget\fR\& \&. \fITarget\fR\& must be \fI?GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\&, \fI?GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\& or \fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\&\&. \fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\& is equivalent to \fI?GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER\fR\& \&.
.LP
The return value is \fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_COMPLETE\fR\& if the framebuffer bound to \fITarget\fR\& is complete\&. Otherwise, the return value is determined as follows:
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_UNDEFINED\fR\& is returned if \fITarget\fR\& is the default framebuffer, but the default framebuffer does not exist\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_INCOMPLETE_ATTACHMENT\fR\& is returned if any of the framebuffer attachment points are framebuffer incomplete\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_INCOMPLETE_MISSING_ATTACHMENT\fR\& is returned if the framebuffer does not have at least one image attached to it\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_INCOMPLETE_DRAW_BUFFER\fR\& is returned if the value of \fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE\fR\& is \fI?GL_NONE\fR\& for any color attachment point(s) named by \fI?GL_DRAWBUFFERi\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_INCOMPLETE_READ_BUFFER\fR\& is returned if \fI?GL_READ_BUFFER\fR\& is not \fI?GL_NONE\fR\& and the value of \fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE\fR\& is \fI?GL_NONE\fR\& for the color attachment point named by \fI?GL_READ_BUFFER\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_UNSUPPORTED\fR\& is returned if the combination of internal formats of the attached images violates an implementation-dependent set of restrictions\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_INCOMPLETE_MULTISAMPLE\fR\& is returned if the value of \fI?GL_RENDERBUFFER_SAMPLES\fR\& is not the same for all attached renderbuffers; if the value of \fI?GL_TEXTURE_SAMPLES\fR\& is the not same for all attached textures; or, if the attached images are a mix of renderbuffers and textures, the value of \fI?GL_RENDERBUFFER_SAMPLES\fR\& does not match the value of \fI?GL_TEXTURE_SAMPLES\fR\& \&.
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_INCOMPLETE_MULTISAMPLE\fR\& is also returned if the value of \fI?GL_TEXTURE_FIXED_SAMPLE_LOCATIONS\fR\& is not the same for all attached textures; or, if the attached images are a mix of renderbuffers and textures, the value of \fI?GL_TEXTURE_FIXED_SAMPLE_LOCATIONS\fR\& is not \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& for all attached textures\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_FRAMEBUFFER_INCOMPLETE_LAYER_TARGETS\fR\& is returned if any framebuffer attachment is layered, and any populated attachment is not layered, or if all populated color attachments are not from textures of the same target\&.
.LP
Additionally, if an error occurs, zero is returned\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
