.RS
.LP
Delete a sync object
.LP
\fIgl:deleteSync\fR\& deletes the sync object specified by \fISync\fR\& \&. If the fence command corresponding to the specified sync object has completed, or if no \fBgl:waitSync/3\fR\& or \fBgl:clientWaitSync/3\fR\& commands are blocking on \fISync\fR\& , the object is deleted immediately\&. Otherwise, \fISync\fR\& is flagged for deletion and will be deleted when it is no longer associated with any fence command and is no longer blocking any \fBgl:waitSync/3\fR\& or \fBgl:clientWaitSync/3\fR\& command\&. In either case, after \fIgl:deleteSync\fR\& returns, the name \fISync\fR\& is invalid and can no longer be used to refer to the sync object\&.
.LP
\fIgl:deleteSync\fR\& will silently ignore a \fISync\fR\& value of zero\&.
