.LP
\fIgl:clientWaitSync\fR\& causes the client to block and wait for the sync object specified by \fISync\fR\& to become signaled\&. If \fISync\fR\& is signaled when \fIgl:clientWaitSync\fR\& is called, \fIgl:clientWaitSync\fR\& returns immediately, otherwise it will block and wait for up to \fITimeout\fR\& nanoseconds for \fISync\fR\& to become signaled\&.
.LP
The return value is one of four status values:
.LP
\fI?GL_ALREADY_SIGNALED\fR\& indicates that \fISync\fR\& was signaled at the time that \fIgl:clientWaitSync\fR\& was called\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TIMEOUT_EXPIRED\fR\& indicates that at least \fITimeout\fR\& nanoseconds passed and \fISync\fR\& did not become signaled\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_CONDITION_SATISFIED\fR\& indicates that \fISync\fR\& was signaled before the timeout expired\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_WAIT_FAILED\fR\& indicates that an error occurred\&. Additionally, an OpenGL error will be generated\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
.B
waitSync(Sync, Flags, Timeout) -> ok
.br
.RS
.LP
