.LP
\fIgl:getSamplerParameter\fR\& returns in \fIParams\fR\& the value or values of the sampler parameter specified as \fIPname\fR\& \&. \fISampler\fR\& defines the target sampler, and must be the name of an existing sampler object, returned from a previous call to \fBgl:genSamplers/1\fR\& \&. \fIPname\fR\& accepts the same symbols as \fBgl:samplerParameteri/3\fR\& , with the same interpretations:
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER\fR\&: Returns the single-valued texture magnification filter, a symbolic constant\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_LINEAR\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER\fR\&: Returns the single-valued texture minification filter, a symbolic constant\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD\fR\&: Returns the single-valued texture minimum level-of-detail value\&. The initial value is -1000\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD\fR\&: Returns the single-valued texture maximum level-of-detail value\&. The initial value is 1000\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S\fR\&: Returns the single-valued wrapping function for texture coordinate s, a symbolic constant\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_REPEAT\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T\fR\&: Returns the single-valued wrapping function for texture coordinate t, a symbolic constant\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_REPEAT\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R\fR\&: Returns the single-valued wrapping function for texture coordinate r, a symbolic constant\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_REPEAT\fR\&\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR\fR\&: Returns four integer or floating-point numbers that comprise the RGBA color of the texture border\&. Floating-point values are returned in the range [0 1]\&. Integer values are returned as a linear mapping of the internal floating-point representation such that 1\&.0 maps to the most positive representable integer and -1\&.0 maps to the most negative representable integer\&. The initial value is (0, 0, 0, 0)\&.
.LP
\fI?GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE\fR\&: Returns a single-valued texture comparison mode, a symbolic constant\&. The initial value is \fI?GL_NONE\fR\&\&. See \fBgl:samplerParameteri/3\fR\& \&.
