.B
endQueryIndexed(Target, Index) -> ok
.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Target = enum()
.br
Index = integer()
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Delimit the boundaries of a query object on an indexed target
.LP
\fIgl:beginQueryIndexed\fR\& and \fBgl:endQueryIndexed/2\fR\& delimit the boundaries of a query object\&. \fIQuery\fR\& must be a name previously returned from a call to \fBgl:genQueries/1\fR\& \&. If a query object with name \fIId\fR\& does not yet exist it is created with the type determined by \fITarget\fR\& \&. \fITarget\fR\& must be one of \fI?GL_SAMPLES_PASSED\fR\&, \fI?GL_ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED\fR\& , \fI?GL_PRIMITIVES_GENERATED\fR\&, \fI?GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_PRIMITIVES_WRITTEN\fR\&, or \fI?GL_TIME_ELAPSED\fR\& \&. The behavior of the query object depends on its type and is as follows\&.
.LP
\fIIndex\fR\& specifies the index of the query target and must be between a \fITarget\fR\& -specific maximum\&.
.LP
If \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_SAMPLES_PASSED\fR\&, \fIId\fR\& must be an unused name, or the name of an existing occlusion query object\&. When \fIgl:beginQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the query object\&'s samples-passed counter is reset to 0\&. Subsequent rendering will increment the counter for every sample that passes the depth test\&. If the value of \fI?GL_SAMPLE_BUFFERS\fR\& is 0, then the samples-passed count is incremented by 1 for each fragment\&. If the value of \fI?GL_SAMPLE_BUFFERS\fR\& is 1, then the samples-passed count is incremented by the number of samples whose coverage bit is set\&. However, implementations, at their discression may instead increase the samples-passed count by the value of \fI?GL_SAMPLES\fR\& if any sample in the fragment is covered\&. When \fIgl:endQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the samples-passed counter is assigned to the query object\&'s result value\&. This value can be queried by calling \fBgl:getQueryObjectiv/2\fR\& with \fIPname\fR\& \fI?GL_QUERY_RESULT\fR\&\&. When \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_SAMPLES_PASSED\fR\&, \fIIndex\fR\& must be zero\&.
.LP
If \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED\fR\&, \fIId\fR\& must be an unused name, or the name of an existing boolean occlusion query object\&. When \fIgl:beginQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the query object\&'s samples-passed flag is reset to \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\&\&. Subsequent rendering causes the flag to be set to \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& if any sample passes the depth test\&. When \fIgl:endQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the samples-passed flag is assigned to the query object\&'s result value\&. This value can be queried by calling \fBgl:getQueryObjectiv/2\fR\& with \fIPname\fR\& \fI?GL_QUERY_RESULT\fR\&\&. When \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED\fR\& , \fIIndex\fR\& must be zero\&.
.LP
If \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_PRIMITIVES_GENERATED\fR\&, \fIId\fR\& must be an unused name, or the name of an existing primitive query object previously bound to the \fI?GL_PRIMITIVES_GENERATED\fR\& query binding\&. When \fIgl:beginQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the query object\&'s primitives-generated counter is reset to 0\&. Subsequent rendering will increment the counter once for every vertex that is emitted from the geometry shader to the stream given by \fIIndex\fR\& , or from the vertex shader if \fIIndex\fR\& is zero and no geometry shader is present\&. When \fIgl:endQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the primitives-generated counter for stream \fIIndex\fR\& is assigned to the query object\&'s result value\&. This value can be queried by calling \fBgl:getQueryObjectiv/2\fR\& with \fIPname\fR\& \fI?GL_QUERY_RESULT\fR\&\&. When \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_PRIMITIVES_GENERATED\fR\& , \fIIndex\fR\& must be less than the value of \fI?GL_MAX_VERTEX_STREAMS\fR\&\&.
.LP
If \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_PRIMITIVES_WRITTEN\fR\&, \fIId\fR\& must be an unused name, or the name of an existing primitive query object previously bound to the \fI?GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_PRIMITIVES_WRITTEN\fR\& query binding\&. When \fIgl:beginQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the query object\&'s primitives-written counter for the stream specified by \fIIndex\fR\& is reset to 0\&. Subsequent rendering will increment the counter once for every vertex that is written into the bound transform feedback buffer(s) for stream \fIIndex\fR\& \&. If transform feedback mode is not activated between the call to \fIgl:beginQueryIndexed\fR\& and \fIgl:endQueryIndexed\fR\&, the counter will not be incremented\&. When \fIgl:endQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the primitives-written counter for stream \fIIndex\fR\& is assigned to the query object\&'s result value\&. This value can be queried by calling \fBgl:getQueryObjectiv/2\fR\& with \fIPname\fR\& \fI?GL_QUERY_RESULT\fR\&\&. When \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_PRIMITIVES_WRITTEN\fR\& , \fIIndex\fR\& must be less than the value of \fI?GL_MAX_VERTEX_STREAMS\fR\&\&.
.LP
If \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TIME_ELAPSED\fR\&, \fIId\fR\& must be an unused name, or the name of an existing timer query object previously bound to the \fI?GL_TIME_ELAPSED\fR\& query binding\&. When \fIgl:beginQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the query object\&'s time counter is reset to 0\&. When \fIgl:endQueryIndexed\fR\& is executed, the elapsed server time that has passed since the call to \fIgl:beginQueryIndexed\fR\& is written into the query object\&'s time counter\&. This value can be queried by calling \fBgl:getQueryObjectiv/2\fR\& with \fIPname\fR\& \fI?GL_QUERY_RESULT\fR\&\&. When \fITarget\fR\& is \fI?GL_TIME_ELAPSED\fR\&, \fIIndex\fR\& must be zero\&.
.LP
Querying the \fI?GL_QUERY_RESULT\fR\& implicitly flushes the GL pipeline until the rendering delimited by the query object has completed and the result is available\&. \fI?GL_QUERY_RESULT_AVAILABLE\fR\& can be queried to determine if the result is immediately available or if the rendering is not yet complete\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
.B
getQueryIndexediv(Target, Index, Pname) -> integer()
.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Target = enum()
.br
Index = integer()
.br
Pname = enum()
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Return parameters of an indexed query object target
.LP
\fIgl:getQueryIndexediv\fR\& returns in \fIParams\fR\& a selected parameter of the indexed query object target specified by \fITarget\fR\& and \fIIndex\fR\& \&. \fIIndex\fR\& specifies the index of the query object target and must be between zero and a target-specific maxiumum\&.
.LP
\fIPname\fR\& names a specific query object target parameter\&. When \fIPname\fR\& is \fI?GL_CURRENT_QUERY\fR\& , the name of the currently active query for the specified \fIIndex\fR\& of \fITarget\fR\& , or zero if no query is active, will be placed in \fIParams\fR\& \&. If \fIPname\fR\& is \fI?GL_QUERY_COUNTER_BITS\fR\& , the implementation-dependent number of bits used to hold the result of queries for \fITarget\fR\& is returned in \fIParams\fR\& \&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
.B
releaseShaderCompiler() -> ok
.br
.RS
.LP
Release resources consumed by the implementation\&'s shader compiler
.LP
\fIgl:releaseShaderCompiler\fR\& provides a hint to the implementation that it may free internal resources associated with its shader compiler\&. \fBgl:compileShader/1\fR\& may subsequently be called and the implementation may at that time reallocate resources previously freed by the call to \fIgl:releaseShaderCompiler\fR\&\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
