.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Program = integer()
.br
BinaryFormat = enum()
.br
Binary = binary()
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Load a program object with a program binary
.LP
\fIgl:programBinary\fR\& loads a program object with a program binary previously returned from \fBgl:getProgramBinary/2\fR\& \&. \fIBinaryFormat\fR\& and \fIBinary\fR\& must be those returned by a previous call to \fBgl:getProgramBinary/2\fR\& , and \fILength\fR\& must be the length returned by \fBgl:getProgramBinary/2\fR\& , or by \fBgl:getProgramiv/2\fR\& when called with \fIPname\fR\& set to \fI?GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_LENGTH\fR\&\&. If these conditions are not met, loading the program binary will fail and \fIProgram\fR\& \&'s \fI?GL_LINK_STATUS\fR\& will be set to \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\&\&.
.LP
A program object\&'s program binary is replaced by calls to \fBgl:linkProgram/1\fR\& or \fIgl:programBinary\fR\& \&. When linking success or failure is concerned, \fIgl:programBinary\fR\& can be considered to perform an implicit linking operation\&. \fBgl:linkProgram/1\fR\& and \fIgl:programBinary\fR\& both set the program object\&'s \fI?GL_LINK_STATUS\fR\& to \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& or \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\& \&.
.LP
A successful call to \fIgl:programBinary\fR\& will reset all uniform variables to their initial values\&. The initial value is either the value of the variable\&'s initializer as specified in the original shader source, or zero if no initializer was present\&. Additionally, all vertex shader input and fragment shader output assignments that were in effect when the program was linked before saving are restored with \fIgl:programBinary\fR\& is called\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
.B
programParameteri(Program, Pname, Value) -> ok
.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Program = integer()
.br
Pname = enum()
.br
Value = integer()
