.RS
.LP
Specify a parameter for a program object
.LP
\fIgl:programParameter\fR\& specifies a new value for the parameter nameed by \fIPname\fR\& for the program object \fIProgram\fR\& \&.
.LP
If \fIPname\fR\& is \fI?GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_RETRIEVABLE_HINT\fR\&, \fIValue\fR\& should be \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\& or \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& to indicate to the implementation the intention of the application to retrieve the program\&'s binary representation with \fBgl:getProgramBinary/2\fR\& \&. The implementation may use this information to store information that may be useful for a future query of the program\&'s binary\&. It is recommended to set \fI?GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_RETRIEVABLE_HINT\fR\& for the program to \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& before calling \fBgl:linkProgram/1\fR\& , and using the program at run-time if the binary is to be retrieved later\&.
.LP
If \fIPname\fR\& is \fI?GL_PROGRAM_SEPARABLE\fR\&, \fIValue\fR\& must be \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\& or \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\& and indicates whether \fIProgram\fR\& can be bound to individual pipeline stages via \fBgl:useProgramStages/3\fR\& \&. A program\&'s \fI?GL_PROGRAM_SEPARABLE\fR\& parameter must be set to \fI?GL_TRUE\fR\&\fIbefore\fR\& \fBgl:linkProgram/1\fR\& is called in order for it to be usable with a program pipeline object\&. The initial state of \fI?GL_PROGRAM_SEPARABLE\fR\& is \fI?GL_FALSE\fR\&\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
